README.md
     1ŌåÆ# xxhash
     6ŌåÆxxhash is a Go implementation of the 64-bit [xxHash] algorithm, XXH64. This is a
     7ŌåÆhigh-quality hashing algorithm that is much faster than anything in the Go
     8ŌåÆstandard library.
     9ŌåÆ
    10ŌåÆThis package provides a straightforward API:
    11ŌåÆ
    12ŌåÆ```
    13ŌåÆfunc Sum64(b []byte) uint64
    14ŌåÆfunc Sum64String(s string) uint64
    15ŌåÆtype Digest struct{ ... }
    16ŌåÆ    func New() *Digest
    17ŌåÆ```
    18ŌåÆ
    19ŌåÆThe `Digest` type implements hash.Hash64. Its key methods are:
    20ŌåÆ
    21ŌåÆ```
    22ŌåÆfunc (*Digest) Write([]byte) (int, error)
    23ŌåÆfunc (*Digest) WriteString(string) (int, error)
    24ŌåÆfunc (*Digest) Sum64() uint64
    25ŌåÆ```
    26ŌåÆ
    27ŌåÆThe package is written with optimized pure Go and also contains even faster
    28ŌåÆassembly implementations for amd64 and arm64. If desired, the `purego` build tag
    29ŌåÆopts into using the Go code even on those architectures.
    30ŌåÆ
    31ŌåÆ[xxHash]: https://xxhash.com/
    32ŌåÆ
    33ŌåÆ## Compatibility
    35ŌåÆThis package is in a module and the latest code is in version 2 of the module.
    36ŌåÆYou need a version of Go with at least "minimal module compatibility" to use
    37ŌåÆgithub.com/cespare/xxhash/v2:
    38ŌåÆ
    39ŌåÆ* 1.9.7+ for Go 1.9
    40ŌåÆ* 1.10.3+ for Go 1.10
    41ŌåÆ* Go 1.11 or later
    42ŌåÆ
    43ŌåÆI recommend using the latest release of Go.
    44ŌåÆ
    45ŌåÆ## Benchmarks
    47ŌåÆHere are some quick benchmarks comparing the pure-Go and assembly
    48ŌåÆimplementations of Sum64.
    49ŌåÆ
    50ŌåÆ| input size | purego    | asm       |
    51ŌåÆ| ---------- | --------- | --------- |
    52ŌåÆ| 4 B        |  1.3 GB/s |  1.2 GB/s |
    53ŌåÆ| 16 B       |  2.9 GB/s |  3.5 GB/s |
    54ŌåÆ| 100 B      |  6.9 GB/s |  8.1 GB/s |
    55ŌåÆ| 4 KB       | 11.7 GB/s | 16.7 GB/s |
    56ŌåÆ| 10 MB      | 12.0 GB/s | 17.3 GB/s |
    57ŌåÆ
    58ŌåÆThese numbers were generated on Ubuntu 20.04 with an Intel Xeon Platinum 8252C
    59ŌåÆCPU using the following commands under Go 1.19.2:
    60ŌåÆ
    61ŌåÆ```
    62ŌåÆbenchstat <(go test -tags purego -benchtime 500ms -count 15 -bench 'Sum64$')
    63ŌåÆbenchstat <(go test -benchtime 500ms -count 15 -bench 'Sum64$')
    64ŌåÆ```
    65ŌåÆ
    66ŌåÆ## Projects using this package
    68ŌåÆ- [InfluxDB](https://github.com/influxdata/influxdb)
    69ŌåÆ- [Prometheus](https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus)
    70ŌåÆ- [VictoriaMetrics](https://github.com/VictoriaMetrics/VictoriaMetrics)
    71ŌåÆ- [FreeCache](https://github.com/coocood/freecache)
    72ŌåÆ- [FastCache](https://github.com/VictoriaMetrics/fastcache)
    73ŌåÆ- [Ristretto](https://github.com/dgraph-io/ristretto)
    74ŌåÆ- [Badger](https://github.com/dgraph-io/badger)
